summary: This document is an email chain from September 10, 2020, between FBI Special Agents discussing the receipt of subpoena returns for a spinoff investigation related to Epstein, and the scheduling of an interview with an individual identified as 'IN'. It shows ongoing investigative activity.

persons.name: Special Agent
persons.context: The primary sender/recipient in the email chain, discussing subpoena returns and scheduling an interview for a spinoff investigation.

events.title: Subpoena Returns Received
events.description: The FBI received subpoena returns related to a spinoff investigation, which were saved and updated to a tracker.

events.title: Discussion of Interview Scheduling
events.description: FBI agents discussed internally and planned to schedule an interview with an individual identified as 'IN' in the coming weeks.

keyFacts: The document is an email chain dated September 10, 2020, concerning a 'spinoff investigation' related to Epstein.
Subpoena returns were received and saved to a specific folder for tracking in the 'Epstein share'.
FBI agents were planning to schedule an interview with an individual referred to as 'IN'.
The correspondence indicates ongoing federal investigative activity in the Epstein case as of mid-2020.
